\intbl \ql \b Summary of Evaluator Report\b0 \line The evaluator indicated that Criteria 3 \'26 4 do not comply with minimum standards and that Criteria 1\'2C 2\'2C 5 and 7 are in need of improvement. \line \line The narrative under Criterion 1 and the conclusion at the end would however suggest that Criterion 1 does not comply with minimum standards.  The evaluator noted that the issue of offering a mixed media programme is really worrying. The evaluator makes the point that too much time will be spent on advertising\'2C which begs the question\'3A how can the diploma be credible as a journalism programme if only one module is allocated to journalism at third-year level\'3F In addition it is noted that the programme seems very old-style\'2C without taking cognisance of the new world of convergence in journalism. Some of the prescribed readings are as old as 1956. To conclude\'2C the evaluator thought that too much is squeezed into this proposed diploma\'2C leading to inadequate time for journalism \'28particularly at third-year level\'29. The Directorate therefore concludes that Criterion 1 does not meet minimum standards. \line \line Other concerns raised by the evaluator are that the student selection and admissions policy is very generic and therefore not adequate\'2C that some language minimum symbol should have been set\'2C that the staff complement is totally inadequate and it would appear as if staffing does not meet the minimum requirements\'2C and that the data on library resources indicates that they are insufficient.  \line \line The Directorate cannot support the recommendation that the programme should be accredited. \line \cell \pard 

